(11148, 118, 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', 'Shipping', 2016, 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'Shipping', 0, '2016-05-17', 10, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the world.Shipping & maritime litigation involves breach of charter-party disputes, cargo and bills of lading claims, the arrest of vessels and cargoes, marine insurance claims, collision, salvage and environmental liabilities. On the non-contentious side, law firms advise on contractual arrangements for construction, financing and registration of vessels, customs and licensing, and documentation relating to charter-parties and bills of lading.', 1, 1, 'Law Firm; Practice Group', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
