(11344, 120, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte', 'Best Places to Work', 2015, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/nomination/64771', '', 0, '2015-11-01', 3, 'The Charlotte Business Journal''s Best Places to Work Awards program recognizes outstanding companies whose benefits, policies and practices are among the best in the region. Your company must have been in business for at least two years.  The company must have 10 or more employees. Company must be located in the Charlotte region. Charlotte region is defined by the following counties: In North Carolina: Alexander, Anson, Cabarrus, Catawba, Cleveland, Gaston, Iredell, Lincoln, Mecklenburg, Rowan, Stanly and Union. In South Carolina: Chester, Chesterfield, Lancaster and York. Step 1- Submit an online nomination: Fill out the form below to submit your nomination to the Charlotte Business Journal. Make sure your company meets the nomination criteria.\n    Step 2- Register with Quantum Workplace: Beginning in early August, you will receive an email from Quantum Workplace that contains a link to access the online employee engagement registration page. Here you will register your company for the survey and receive your company''s organization code and the address of the survey website.', 0, 0, 'Law Firm; Company; Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3982, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11345, 120, '', '40 Under 40', 2015, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/event/93971', '', 0, '2015-12-01', 3, 'The Charlotte Business Journal is recognizing the Charlotte region’s 40 Under 40. These are 40 individuals under the age of 40 who are making major strides in their careers and having a positive impact on their communities.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3983, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11346, 120, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte', 'Healthiest Employers of Greater Charlotte Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/nomination/79342?ana=et_clt_healthiestnom#eligibility', 'Recognition: Honorees and winners will be recognized at an awards program and in a special publication of the Charlotte Business Journal on November 2014.\n    Free Survey Overview Report: You will get a free report on your company''s survey results, w', 0, '2016-03-11', 3, 'The Charlotte Business Journal''s annual Healthiest Employers of Greater Charlotte Awards program honors local companies with outstanding health and wellness initiatives. We''re looking for organizations that are committed to creating a healthy workplace and making wellness a priority and proactively shaping the health of their employees. Nominate your company today to see how your wellness program measures up to the competition! Company must be located in the Charlotte region. Charlotte region is defined by the following counties: In North Carolina: Alexander, Anson, Cabarrus, Catawba, Cleveland, Gaston, Iredell, Lincoln, Mecklenburg, Rowan, Stanly and Union. In South Carolina: Chester, Chesterfield, Lancaster and York', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3984, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11347, 120, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte', 'Women in Business Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/nomination/79372#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-03-27', 3, 'Recognize the successes of professional women in the Charlotte area by submitting a nomination for the 20th Annual Women in Business Achievement Awards program. We''re looking for women from every industry and profession — women who have made a difference in their workplace and are blazing trails for other women.\n\nThe 25 winners and Lifetime Achievement Award winner will be recognized at a special awards celebration on June 16, 2016 and will be profiled in the June 17 publication of the Charlotte Business Journal.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3985, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11348, 120, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte', 'CFO of the Year Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/nomination/79482#eligibility', 'Recognition: Honorees and winners will be recognized at an awards program and in a special publication of the Charlotte Business Journal on November 2014.\n    Free Survey Overview Report: You will get a free report on your company''s survey results, w', 0, '2016-04-17', 3, 'The Charlotte Business Journal''s 2016 CFO of the Year Awards will be given to top local professionals with outstanding performance in their roles as senior financial leaders.\nEligibility:\nNominee must be a Chief Financial Officer or hold an equivalent title at the time of the nomination.\nExecutives who do not carry a CFO designation are eligible as long as they are the top finance executive in the company.\nNominee must have served a minimum period of three years as CFO or equivalent title. This doesn''t require holding the title for 3+ years at the same company, just 3+ years during their career.\nNominee must reside and work in one of the 16 counties in the Charlotte area: The Charlotte area is defined by the following counties: Alexander, Anson, Cabarrus, Catawba, Chester, Chesterfield, Cleveland, Gaston, Iredell, Lancaster, Lincoln, Mecklenburg, Rowan, Stanly, Union and York.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3986, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
