(11350, 121, '', 'Fast 55 Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-02-29', 4, 'The Business Courier needs your help in identifying Greater Cincinnati''s fastest-growing companies. To be eligible for Fast 55, a company must:\nbe independent, for-profit and privately held;\nbe headquartered in the 17-county, three-state Greater Cincinnati region;\nhave a three-year operating history;\nhave an average of at least $1 million in sales for the three most recent years, with no year less than $200,000.', 0, 1, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3988, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11351, 121, '', 'C-Suite Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-05-06', 4, 'The C-Suite Awards recognizes Greater Cincinnati''s top executives for their contribution and commitment to the community and their outstanding professional performance.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3989, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11352, 121, '', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-06-03', 4, 'Young professionals are a vital asset to our region and it is important to acknowledge those who are making great strides in shaping our community''s future. Since 1995, the Business Courier has recognized our region''s young talent through our annual Forty Under 40 awards.\nEach year through our open nominations process, we seek forty individuals, under the age of 40, who are making a difference in business and community. The emphasis is on leadership and potential leadership- whether it is in business, politics, the arts, nonprofits, education, health care or public service. Focus is also placed on the nominee''s community involvement. Think of your friends, family, colleagues, clients -- anyone who matches the criteria -- and nominate as many as you''d like.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3990, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11353, 121, '', 'Second Act Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-06-03', 4, 'The days of working for a single company for your entire life are over. Many are starting fresh, either joining existing companies with a new career or starting their own challenge. \nThe Business Courier is proud to announce the Second Act awards, honoring Cincinnatians who have found success after a first career, as either owner or manager. \nThe target age for our honorees will be at, near, or above 60 years.\nAll nominees must be residents of the 17-county, three state Greater Cincinnati region. These counties include: Ohio - Brown, Butler, Clermont, Clinton, Hamilton, Highland and Warren; Kentucky - Boone, Bracken, Campbell, Gallatin, Grant, Kenton, and Pendleton; Indiana - Dearborn, Franklin, and Ohio.   ', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3991, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11354, 121, '', 'Outstanding Board Excellence', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-07-15', 4, 'During the nomination and selection process we heard from many CEO’s and owners that they felt it was not fair for them to nominate only one board member so after discussion we have decided to add a category for “Board Excellence”. This award will take into consideration your entire outside board of directors. It will be a group award and will focus on two qualifying questions;\n\nWhat distinguishes your board’s accomplishments from those of its peers\nWhat impact has your board had on the company or organization', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3992, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11355, 121, '', 'Outstanding Director Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-07-15', 4, 'The 2016 Outstanding Director Awards will honor directors who have significantly influenced boardroom practices and performance; and who lead with innovation, courage and commitment.\n\nThe awards underscore the critical role that directors play in terms of best governance practices that build and sustain stakeholder value.\n\nHonorees are top board governance leaders whose leadership skills have helped guide their company’s success and who raise the bar for governance best practices in the boardrooms in our community.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3993, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11356, 121, '', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', 0, '2016-08-19', 4, 'Help the Business Courier identify and recognize the Cincinnati-area employers that have the most engaged workforces. A special publication will be created by the Courier profiling the finalists and winners.\nThe format is an online, anonymous survey of employees consisting of about 50 questions. The survey is conducted through an independent market research company Quantum Workplace.\nThe contest is open to any company located in the 17-county Greater Cincinnati region with more than 10 employees.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3994, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11357, 122, '', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and th', 0, '2016-02-26', 4, 'Columbus Business First invites you to nominate individuals for this prestigious award! Forty Under 40 honorees will be highlighted in a special supplement published in the May 27, 2016 issue of Business First.\n\nThe longest-running awards program at Business First, Forty Under 40 is in its 24th year and recognizes young “movers and shakers” in the community. The 40 honorees, who are under the age of 40, are judged on their outstanding career achievements and community service.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3995, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11358, 122, '', 'Corporate Caring Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and th', 0, '2016-04-08', 4, 'The Corporate Caring Awards Program honors for-profit companies for their financial contributions, volunteer service and other unique contributions to Columbus'' charities and nonprofit organizations.There are five award categories in which judges choose one small, one medium, and one large company. The categories represent the type of nonprofits in which a company focuses their giving, based on the information provided. ', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3996, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11359, 122, '', 'C-Suite Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and th', 0, '2016-05-16', 4, 'The C-Suite Awards honor C-level executives of for profit companies, nonprofits and government agencies for their unique contributions to their organizations and to the Central Ohio community.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3997, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
