(11360, 122, '', 'Fast 50 Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', 'Financial information used to compile the rankings is kept confidential by our accounting partner and is not made available to Business First or other sponsors of the Fast 50 program. Sales-growth percentage is calculated by subtracting revenue two y', 0, '2016-07-01', 4, '2016 will mark the 21st anniversary of the Fast 50 Awards in Columbus. We invite you to submit an application to Columbus Business First''s Fast 50 Program.\nELIGIBILITY\nAll nominees must:\nBe independent, for-profit and privately held\nHave an average of at least $1 million in revenue per year for the past three years\nBe headquartered the Central Ohio region  (Delaware, Fairfield, Franklin, Hocking, Licking, Madison, Morrow, Perry, Pickaway or Union counties)\nHave a three-year operating sales history', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3998, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11361, 122, '', 'Best Places to Work Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/62831', '', 0, '2016-07-22', 4, 'Think you''re employed at one of the best places to work in Central Ohio? You’re in the right place!  Filling out this form will begin the registration process for 2016 Best Places to Work research project.  Please read the following details carefully and complete the nomination form. We will use this contact information in mid-July 2016 to verify your continued interest in participating in the program.\n \nThe Best Places to Work program highlights companies in Central Ohio whose operations are changing the business landscape.  Business First will profile those who are doing their best to foster a great workplace. Last year, 235 companies entered and the top 51 were honored at a high energy luncheon. Don''t miss out -- nominate your company today!', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3999, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11362, 122, '', 'BizTech Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/62831', '', 0, '2016-09-16', 4, 'Help Columbus Business First recognize the people, organizations and companies making an impact on technology and innovation in our community. The BizTech Awards celebrate those contributing to a culture of technology leadership and innovation in the Columbus region. Nominate individuals and organizations that contribute to the Columbus region’s growing reputation as a leader in technology innovation.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4000, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11363, 123, 'http://www.dailybusinessreview.com/', 'On the Rise', 2015, 'http://pdfserver.amlaw.com/dbr/2015-On-the-Rise-Nomination-Form.pdf', '', 0, '2015-06-01', 3, 'The DBR On The Rise program recognizes the region’s 40 most promising lawyers under the age of 40 as of Jan. To qualify, the lawyers must work in South Florida. Nominations should be sent to dbrrecognition@alm.com. We''re looking for lawyers who have wielded influence in their practice areas in South Florida\nand beyond. They should be innovators, developing unique practice niches, amassing robust\nbooks of business, demonstrating strong leadership qualities, showing expertise in litigation or\ntransactional work, and committing themselves to pro bono, charitable and professional\nvolunteer work.\nFor this contest, we are asking you to provide:\n1. An essay of no more than 500 words describing why the nominee should be selected. Among\nthe questions that you should attempt to answer:\n• What accomplishments in the last year qualify the nominee for our list? What makes the\nnominee stand out from his or her peers?\n• How has the nominee demonstrated leadership — in their practice, in the workplace and\nin the profession?\n• Has the nominee contributed to the community through pro bono work, charitable work\nor public service? Please describe.\n2. A biography of the nominee, including the following information:\n• Employer\n• Title\n• City and state\n• Birthdates\n• Educations\n• Legal work experience including notable cases, transactions and clients, dates and\nemployer names\n• Other relevant information such as awards, affiliations and significant publications\n3. A high-resolution photo of the nominee.\n4. Contact information for two references who can be contacted for an on-the-record\nconversation about the nominee’s legal work and accomplishments.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4001, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11364, 124, 'https://www.dailyjournal.com/public/PubMain.cfm', 'Top Plaintiff Lawyers', 2015, 'https://www.dailyjournal.com/public/PubMain.cfm?seloption=nomsub&pubdate=showRtBar&shNewsType=nomsub&NewsId=-1&sdivId=&screenHt=770', 'Personal Injury: Plaintiff; Data Security; Fraud', 0, '2015-06-12', 5, 'In this inaugural list of top plaintiff lawyers, the Daily Journal seeks to honor lawyers bringing single cases and multi-party actions in antitrust, labor & employment, environment, personal injury, privacy and data security, product defect and securities and financial fraud. In deciding whether/whom to submit, remember we are looking for impact. How did this attorney’s work impact an industry? The law? The government? Society? All of these questions should be explored and answered in this survey. Matters concerning major issues of the day (making state/national headlines, or cases the industry is following) are given special consideration.\nWe understand many matters are sensitive; however, you must provide the names of matters and clients for all work to be considered for this nomination. We will only contact clients for interviews if the nominee is selected to the list.\nNo extensions to the deadline will be granted. Photos are appreciated but not required. They should be named with the nominee''s last name and bar number and emailed to nominations@dailyjournal.com with the nominee''s full name and bar number in the email subject line.\nNominees must be California Bar members in good standing and based in California although their work can be anywhere in the world.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11365, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'Who''s Who in DFW Health Care', 2015, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'Health care', 0, '2015-06-12', 3, 'We''re looking for the most influential business people in North Texas health care. Eligibility Requirements\n\nEveryone knows it takes great doctors and outstanding nurses to deliver top-flight medical care. Less celebrated is the extensive business-to-business network that makes our health care system tick.\n\nConsider nominating North Texas leaders who specialize in the business aspects of health care. Nominees may be entrepreneurs or executives in any field, including accounting, consulting, device manufacturing, diagnostic services, education, finance, information technology, insurance, law, pharmacy, professional and trade organizations, public policy, real estate and staffing.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: The judges will base their decisions solely on the information provided on the nomination forms. Provide detailed information so the judges can give the nominee full consideration. You may wish to print out the nomination form first and review the questions before submitting your responses online.\n\nPrevious winners of this award are eligible to win again, however their nomination must demonstrate why they are still relevent as well as any new achievements and accomplishments since their previous win.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4002, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11366, 125, '', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination/', '', 0, '2016-03-15', 3, 'The Dallas Business Journal is searching for executives and entrepreneurs in the North Texas business community under the age of 40 for our annual 40 Under 40 Awards. To qualify, nominees must be 39 years old or younger as of May 20, 2016. Tell us about your nominee''s proven track record in both business and community involvement. We are looking for executives who stand out — innovators, deal makers and heavy hitters who excel in their companies and industries and still make time for their communities.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4003, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11367, 125, '', 'Middle Market 50', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination/', '', 0, '2016-04-22', 3, 'This second annual research project of the Dallas Business Journal ranks the fastest-growing companies in Dallas-Fort Worth with annual revenue of $25 million to $750 million, based on revenue growth over a three-year period.\n\nTo participate, companies must provide revenue figures for 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2015 for use in calculating the percentage of revenue growth during that period. This information will be published in the final Middle Market 50 list.\nBoth private and public companies are eligible to participate. Companies must be headquartered in North Texas. Regional offices or subsidiaries will not be considered for this particular list. ', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4004, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11368, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', '', 0, '2016-05-20', 3, 'Nominate your company for the Dallas Business Journal''s 14th annual Best Places to Work Awards!\nEligibility Requirements\nTo get started, complete this form and follow the steps below. You''ll find answers to frequently asked questions below, as well. \nIn order to be considered, your company must have a minimum of 10 employees in the seven-county North Texas region: Dallas, Collin, Denton, Tarrant, Rockwall, Ellis and Kaufman counties. Company headquarters may be elsewhere. Eligibility is determined solely by the number of North Texas employees.', 0, 0, 'Company; Law Firm; Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4005, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11369, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'Women in Business Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', '', 0, '2016-06-10', 3, 'The Dallas Business Journal''s ninth annual Women in Business Awards will honor the North Texas'' most influential business women. We''re looking for women from every industry and profession — women who have made a difference in their workplace, blaze trails for other women and are leaving a mark on their communities. ', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4006, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11370, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'Women in Technology Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', '', 0, '2016-07-29', 3, 'The Dallas Business Journal’s 2016 North Texas Women in Technology Awards honor tech-focused women who drive innovation, lead technology companies and shape the local community.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4007, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11371, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'CFO of the Year Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', '', 0, '2016-08-19', 3, 'Nominees should be either a chief financial officer or hold an equivalent position at a company or organization based in North Texas.. The CFO of the Year Awards are given to the chief financial officers and their teams who deliver the most outstanding performances for their companies. A panel of independent judges, drawn from the region''s top financial leaders, will determine the winners based on criteria that will include:\nDemonstrated financial growth during the year\nSuccess in overcoming significant business challenges or barriers\nExamples of team leadership and superior management\nOther factors may include a chief financial officer''s contributions to the community (such as social, nonprofit or charitable giving)\nDemonstrated commitment to the company''s financial best practices and accounting standards, or success as a strategic visionary for the enterprise', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4008, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11372, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'Who''s Who in Energy', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', '', 0, '2016-09-02', 3, 'The Dallas Business Journal is seeking nominations for the multistate ''Who''s Who in Energy'' publication.\n\nBusiness journals in multiple cities — Dallas, Denver, Houston, Pittsburgh, St. Louis and San Antonio — will partner on this undertaking. The result? A listing of some 700 business leaders across sectors and states who are making energy deals happen and/or working on behalf of energy companies. The list will be published in the Nov. 27 issue of the DBJ.\n \nHonorees can work in a number of positions throughout the energy industry, including finance, law, engineering and energy companies themselves.', 1, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4009, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11373, 125, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'Outstanding Directors Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', '', 0, '2016-09-09', 3, 'The 2016 Outstanding Directors Awards honor individual directors and full boards of directors that demonstrate the vital leadership and business savvy necessary to help guide their businesses’ success.   C-level executives or significant business partners (such as accounting firms, bankers, law firms, compensation advisers and other consultants) are the ideal nominators for this prestigious award recognizing high-performing directors or boards. We welcome nominations from anyone with first-hand knowledge of a board’s or board member’s achievements.\n   ', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4010, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11374, 126, '', 'Financial and Corporate Research', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-04-15', 10, 'The IFLR1000 Financial and corporate research is now entering its 27th annual edition and we invite all relevant law firms to participate in the process.\nThe research process culminates in the publication of law firm rankings, individual lawyer recommendations and law firm reviews (IFLR1000 Reviews).\nThe Financial and corporate research incorporates the following practice areas:\nBanking and finance (banking, financial restructuring, project finance)\nCapital markets (debt, derivatives, equity, structured finance and securitisation)\nCompetition *\nCorporate and M&A (M&A and private equity)\nFinancial services regulatory *\nInvestment funds *\nRestructuring and insolvency', 1, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4011, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
