(11436, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'Global 20', 2015, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', '', 0, '2015-05-08', 11, 'For the fifth year, Law360 will profile the 20 law firms with the greatest global reach\nand expertise. To arrive at the Global 20 list, Law360 will rank participating firms in five\ncategories: 1) the number of countries where the firm has offices, 2) the number of offices\noutside the firm’s home country, 3) the percentage of attorneys working outside the firm’s home\ncountry, 4) the breadth of the firm’s recent international work and 5) the size and complexity of\nthe firm’s recent cross-border work. ', 1, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4073, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11437, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'Pro Bono Firm of the Year', 2015, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', 'Pro bono', 0, '2015-06-24', 11, 'Law360 will profile the firms that had the biggest wins in pro bono\ncases. Submissions must be no more than 1,500 words, and an accurate word count\nmust be included. They should include the average number of pro bono hours contributed per\nattorney in the past year; a concise description of the biggest wins the firm had in pro bono\ncases from May 1, 2014, to May 1, 2015; and the dates and significance of those wins. Law360\nwill select up to 20 firms to be profiled as part of this series. Submission forms should be titled with the firm’s name. Send submissions to\neditor@law360.com with the email subject line, “Pro Bono: Firm Name.” ', 1, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4074, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11438, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'Most Feared Plaintiffs Firms', 2015, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', 'Plaintiffs', 0, '2015-08-05', 11, 'Law360 will profile the plaintiffs firms that strike fear in the hearts of\ncounsel across the aisle. Submissions must be no more than 1,500 words, and an accurate\nword count must be included. They should detail the firm’s major wins in litigation from July 1,\n2014, to July 1, 2015. Explain the significance of these wins and specify key dates as well as \nthe role the firm played in each matter. Submissions should also include contact information for\nthree references — clients or opposing counsel — who are willing to be interviewed should we\nselect your firm to profile. If you think your firm leaves others quaking in their boots, send your submission titled with the\nfirm’s name to editor@law360.com with the email subject line, “Most Feared Firms: Firm Name.” ', 1, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4075, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11439, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'Practice Group of the Year', 2016, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', '', 0, '2015-09-18', 11, 'Law360 is pleased to announce its second annual data-driven rankings of practice groups.\nGroups in several leading practice areas will be honored and some will be profiled. Unlike our\nPractice Groups of the Year awards, these rankings will be based solely on quantifiable data. Law360’s Practice Groups of the Year highlights up to five practice groups that notched the biggest litigation victories or deals of the year. Winners are recognized for the size, complexity and significance of the deals or litigation they worked on. ', 1, 1, '3', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'subscribed', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2016-03-30 18:14:20'),
(11440, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'MVPs of the Year', 2015, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', '', 0, '2015-10-07', 11, 'Law360’s MVPs of the Year recognizes the five attorneys who had extraordinary wins and contributed most to their practice area in the past year. The series showcases standout attorneys across the practice areas and industries covered by Law360. We will accept nominations for attorneys in the following practice areas: aerospace & defense, appellate, automotive, capital markets, banking, bankruptcy, class action, competition/antitrust, consumer protection, employment, energy, environmental, food & beverage, government contracts, health care, hospitality, insurance, intellectual property, international trade, life sciences, media & entertainment, mergers & acquisitions, privacy, private equity, product liability, project finance, real estate, retail & e-commerce, securities, tax, technology, and white collar. Submissions must be no more than 1,500 words, and an accurate word count must be included. They should provide a concise description of the attorney’s achievements from Oct.1, 2014, to Oct. 1, 2015, for example, wins at trial or on appeal, successful use of a novel defense, etc. For each achievement listed, note the date, the significance and what role the attorney played. Firms are limited to two nominees per practice group.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4077, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11441, 129, 'https://www.law360.com/', 'Practice Groups of the Year', 2015, 'https://www.law360.com/Law360-2015-Editorial-Calendar.pdf', '', 0, '2015-11-04', 11, 'Law360 will profile those practice groups that achieved the biggest wins in the most important\ncases or worked on the biggest deals. We will profile up to 10 firms for each of the following\npractice areas: aerospace & defense, appellate, automotive, capital markets, banking,\nbankruptcy, class action, competition/antitrust, consumer protection, employment, energy,\nenvironmental, food & beverage, government contracts, health care, hospitality, insurance,\nintellectual property, international trade, life sciences, media & entertainment, mergers &\nacquisitions, privacy, private equity, product liability, project finance, real estate, retail & ecommerce,\nsecurities, tax, technology, and white collar.  Submissions must be no more than 1,500 words, and an accurate word count must be\nincluded. Each submission should detail the group’s major successes from Oct. 1, 2014, to\nOct. 1, 2015, for example, U.S. Supreme Court wins or appeals granted, major transactions \nworked on, etc. For each case or deal the firm worked on, please note the date, significance\nand what role the firm played: lead counsel, local counsel, etc. We cannot weigh your\nsubmission properly without this information. Winners will be selected based on: 1) the\nsignificance of the litigation wins or deals worked on, 2) the size and complexity of the litigation\nwins or the deals worked on and 3) the number of significant, large or complex deals the firms\nworked on or lawsuits the firm had wins in.\neditor@law360.com', 0, 1, 'Legal Department; Practice Group', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4078, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11442, 130, '', 'Legal 500 Asia Pacific', 2017, '', '', 0, '2016-05-20', 8, 'THE LEGAL 500 ASIA PACIFIC 2017 EDITION TIMETABLE\nClient referees deadline: Friday 20 May 2016\nEditorial submission deadline: Friday 20 May 2016\nDetails of researchers will be published on Monday 13 June 2016\n\nFirm interviews conducted: 13 June and 29 July 2016\nLATE REFEREES\nThe Legal 500 series contacted over 280,000 individual referees in 2015. To ensure referees are not repeatedly contacted, it takes time to process and de-duplicate the spreadsheets. As such, it is imperative that referees are submitted by the specified deadlines in the Timetables section below. Please note the following rules and deadlines for late referees:\n\nAny referees received between 21 May 2016 and 3 June 2016 will be contacted only if that individual has not already been submitted in a spreadsheet by any firm before 20 May 2016. This is to help ensure that referees do not receive multiple emails from us.\n\nAny referees submitted after 3 June 2016 will not be contacted.\n- See more at: http://www.legal500.com/assets/pages/about-us/get-involved.html#sthash.BND2cvrq.dpuf', 1, 1, '3', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2016-03-30 18:02:39'),
(11443, 130, 'http://www.legal500.com/assets/pages/awards/uk/2014/home.html', 'Banking (In-house)', 2016, 'http://www.legal500.com/assets/pages/awards/uk/2014/home.html', 'In house;', 0, '2016-02-29', 10, 'The Legal 500 United Kingdom Awards is a concept that recognises and rewards the best in-house and private practice teams and individuals over the past 12 months. There are no submissions, or black tie dinners that cost thousands of dollars to attend - the awards are handed to the elite legal practitioners, based on the most comprehensive research into the UK legal market. Over 50,000 interviews were conducted to ascertain the winners, who were invited to a free networking dinner in London to celebrate with their peers.', 1, 1, '4', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2016-03-30 18:03:57'),
