(11550, 131, 'http://libn.com/', '50 Around 50', 2015, 'http://libn.com/around-50-awards-sept/around-50-nomination-form/', '', 0, '2015-06-13', 2, 'Past the cut-off for our 40 Under 40 Awards?\n\nBorn somewhere in the 50s – give or take – and are nowhere near being ready to hang up your spurs?\n\nThat makes you Around 50. What better reason to celebrate?\n\nJoin Long Island Business News – born in 1953 – as we celebrate the companies and business leaders who are around 50 and proud of it.\n\nThe 2013 celebration event was held on on Sept. 19 at the Crest Hollow Country Club in Woodbury and included awards for our special honorees, a keepsake special print section, online coverage, plus music and merriment … until curfew.\nNOMINEE MUST BE somewhere around 50', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11551, 131, 'http://libn.com/', 'Top 50 Women', 2015, 'http://libn.com/influential-women/top-50-women-nomination-form/', '', 0, '2015-07-03', 2, 'Launched in 2000, the Top 50 Most Influential Women in Business program has recognized the Island’s top women professionals for business acumen, mentoring and community involvement. The program’s honorees are selected by a judging committee and receive a unique crystal memento at the elegant dinner attended by more than 600 of the Island’s top business leaders, and represent the most influential women in business, government and the not-for-profit fields', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11552, 131, 'http://libn.com/', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://libn.com/40-under-40-awards-january-2/40-under-40-nomination-form/', '', 0, '2015-10-16', 2, 'Long Island’s most promising business people are the movers and shakers under the age of 40, working toward success and improving our business community every step of the way. Join us in our annual salute to Long Island’s rising stars.\nNOMINEE MUST BE UNDER THE AGE OF 40 PRIOR TO THE DATE OF THE EVENT. REFER TO EVENT PAGE FOR DATE OF EVENT.\nTo nominate yourself, a colleague, client, business associate or friend for Long Island Business News'' 40 Under 40 Award - please complete the form below by first selecting which type of nomination you are submitting ~ for yourself or for another; next step is entering information on the person you are nominating; and then entering your own contact information.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4186, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11553, 131, 'http://libn.com/', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://libn.com/40-under-40-awards-january-2/40-under-40-nomination-form/', '', 0, '2016-10-17', 2, 'Long Island’s most promising business people are the movers and shakers under the age of 40, working toward success and improving our business community every step of the way. Join us in our annual salute to Long Island’s rising stars.\nNOMINEE MUST BE UNDER THE AGE OF 40 PRIOR TO THE DATE OF THE EVENT. REFER TO EVENT PAGE FOR DATE OF EVENT.\nTo nominate yourself, a colleague, client, business associate or friend for Long Island Business News'' 40 Under 40 Award - please complete the form below by first selecting which type of nomination you are submitting ~ for yourself or for another; next step is entering information on the person you are nominating; and then entering your own contact information.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4187, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11554, 132, '', 'Women in Business: Career Achievement Award', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/twincities/nomination/79532', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 4, 'The Career Achievement Award will recognize a female executive''s leadership, exceptional performance in her field and involvement in the Twin Cities business community.  To be eligible, nominees must work in the 24-county Twin Cities metro area, including Anoka, Benton, Blue Earth, Carver, Chisago, Dakota, Freeborn, Goodhue, Hennepin, Isanti, Le Sueur, Mower, Nicollet, Olmsted, Ramsey, Rice, Scott, Sherburne, Stearns, Steele, Washington, Wright, Pierce and St. Croix counties.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4188, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11555, 133, 'http://nydailyrecord.com/', 'Attorneys of the Year', 2015, 'http://nydailyrecord.com/attorneys-of-the-year/', '', 0, '2015-09-14', 2, 'The Daily Record’s Attorneys of the Year Awards honors outstanding attorneys — through the Leaders in Law award — and general counsel with the Top Counsel award.  One outstanding attorney will be awarded the prestigious Nathaniel Award, which goes to a lawyer who regularly goes above and beyond the call of duty in the name of justice. All of these awards are given to attorneys who demonstrate professional accomplishment, exceptional character, integrity and ethics and commitment to their clients and the community.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4189, 'subscribed/ nominations open until the date given', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11556, 134, '', 'Root/Stimson Award', 0, 'http://www.nysba.org/CustomTemplates/SecondaryStandard.aspx?id=32366', '', 0, '2016-05-02', 2, 'The Root/Stimson Award honors a lawyer who has demonstrated outstanding commitment to community and volunteer service and to the improvement of the justice system. Named for Elihu Root and Henry L. Stimson to honor their commitment to public service, this award is presented to a lawyer admitted to practice in New York state who is actively involved in volunteer community service work. The award recognizes members of the legal profession who have given unstintingly of their time through community service activities. NOTE: The committee is not seeking nominees who have provided pro bono legal services representation. Those nominations should be submitted for consideration to the President''s Committee on Access to Justice which administers the annual pro bono award.', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4190, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11557, 134, 'https://www.nysba.org', ' Ruth G. Schapiro Memorial Award', 2016, 'http://www.nysba.org/CustomTemplates/Content.aspx?id=27257', '', 0, '2015-11-02', 2, 'To honor a male or female member of the Association who has made a noteworthy contribution to the concerns of women through pro bono services, writing, service to bar associations or community organizations or other such endeavors.   Person must be a member of the NYSBA and must have made a noteworthy contribution to the concerns of women through activities stated above. ', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4191, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11558, 134, 'https://www.nysba.org', 'Kay Crawford Murray Award ', 2016, 'https://www.nysba.org/CustomTemplates/Content.aspx?id=27256', '', 0, '2015-11-02', 2, 'To honor women in the profession who recognize the value of diversity in the legal profession and have dedicated their time to advancing the professional development of women attorneys. Future recipients will possess the following characteristics: a distinguished legal career or a rising star in the profession; an active member of bar associations for the purpose of advancing the professional and personal development of women attorneys; an active mentor to women attorneys.    The award was developed and is administered by the Committee on Women\nin the Law. Future recipients will possess the following characteristics:\n(1) a distinguished legal career or a rising\nstar in the profession;\n(2) an active member of one or more\nbar associations for the purpose of\nadvancing the professional and personal\ndevelopment of women attorneys;\n(3) an active mentor to women attorneys;\nand\n(4) a substantial contributor to increasing\nthe value of diversity in the legal\nProfession. ', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4192, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11559, 134, 'https://www.nysba.org', ' Outstanding Young Lawyer Award ', 2016, 'https://www.nysba.org/oyl/', '', 0, '2015-11-06', 2, 'Each year, the Young Lawyers Section of the New York State\nBar Association honors a young lawyer who has rendered\noutstanding service to both the community and the legal\nprofession. The Outstanding Young Lawyer Award recognizes\nan attorney who has actively practiced less than ten years and has a distinguished record of\ncommitment to the finest traditions of the Bar through public service and professional activities.\nThese activities may include, but are not limited to pro bono service, service to bar associations\nand community organizations, and participation in those activities that enhance the profession\nand benefit the public.\nThe award will be presented at the Young Lawyers Section Executive Committee Meeting during\nthe New York State Bar Association Annual Meeting in January 2016.\nEligibility and Award Criteria\n• Nominees must be admitted to practice in New York State and have practiced less than ten\nyears at the time of nomination. Membership in the NYSBA is not required.\n• Nominees must be involved primarily in the active practice of law as distinguished from\nan attorney who has been primarily engaged in business, or as a legislator, or other holder\nof public office or position, where admission to the Bar is not required.\n• Service in a public service position such as district attorney, assistant district attorney,\nattorney general, assistant attorney general, judgeships, or judicial clerkships will be\nincluded for determining years of practice, but will not be considered community\nor professional service.\n• Members of the New York State Bar Association Young Lawyers Section Executive\nCommittee and past chairpersons of the Section are not eligible for nomination.\n• All submissions require a completed nomination form. Please attach additional sheets,\nif necessary.\n• Letters and a resume supporting the nomination will be considered, if they enhance the\ninformation provided in the nomination form', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4193, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11560, 134, 'https://www.nysba.org', 'Award for Attorney Professionalism', 2016, 'https://www.nysba.org/AttorneyProfessionalism/', '', 0, '2015-11-16', 2, 'To honor a member of the NYSBA for outstanding professionalism, which is defined as dedication to service to clients and a commitment to promoting respect for the legal system in pursuit of justice and the public good, characterized by exemplary ethical conduct, competence, good judgment, integrity and civility   . Attorney professionalism is dedication to service to clients and a commitment to promoting respect for the legal system in pursuit of justice and the public good, characterized by exemplary ethical conduct, competence, good judgment, integrity and civility.\n\nThe Award honors attorneys who evidence the highest attributes of professionalism in the practice of law: attorneys who have labored in “the vineyard” and are especially valued by their clients and their colleagues. Therefore, rather than a lifetime achievement award, this particular honor relates to professionalism in the actual practice of law. Background letters from clients, other attorneys and judges have provided a full picture for the reviewing committee in the past. Your nomination should, as inclusively as possible, specify how the nominee has demonstrated the following attributes:\n\na) Dedication to service to clients and always acting in the best interests of the client;\n\nb) Civility: behaving to all with courtesy, consideration and respect;\n\nc) Exemplary ethical conduct: endeavoring at all times to fulfill the spirit, and not just the requirements, of the NY Rules of Professional Conduct;\n\nd) Competence: keeping abreast of the latest developments in his or her area of practice;\n\ne) Good judgment: providing client service consisting of discerning opinions and advice based upon knowledge, experience, moral as well as legal considerations;\n\nf) Mentoring, educating and assisting other attorneys;\n\ng) Integrity: always exhibiting soundness of character, fidelity, honesty and fairness.\n\n\nPlease keep in mind, in considering your nomination, that there are other awards honoring service to bar associations and pro bono activities. In this Attorney Professionalism Award, the New York State Bar Association seeks to honor a person who exemplifies the highest standards of professionalism in the actual practice of law. ', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4194, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11561, 134, 'https://www.nysba.org', ' Outstanding Young Lawyer Award ', 2016, 'https://www.nysba.org/oyl/', '', 0, '2016-11-07', 2, 'Each year, the Young Lawyers Section of the New York State Bar Association honors a young lawyer who has rendered outstanding service to both the community and the legal\nprofession. The Outstanding Young Lawyer Award recognizes an attorney who has actively practiced less than ten years and has a distinguished record of commitment to the finest traditions of the Bar through public service and professional activities.\nThese activities may include, but are not limited to pro bono service, service to bar associations and community organizations, and participation in those activities that enhance the profession and benefit the public.\nThe award will be presented at the Young Lawyers Section Executive Committee Meeting during the New York State Bar Association Annual Meeting in January 2016.\nEligibility and Award Criteria\n• Nominees must be admitted to practice in New York State and have practiced less than ten years at the time of nomination. Membership in the NYSBA is not required.\n• Nominees must be involved primarily in the active practice of law as distinguished from an attorney who has been primarily engaged in business, or as a legislator, or other holder of public office or position, where admission to the Bar is not required.\n• Service in a public service position such as district attorney, assistant district attorney,\nattorney general, assistant attorney general, judgeships, or judicial clerkships will be\nincluded for determining years of practice, but will not be considered community\nor professional service.\n• Members of the New York State Bar Association Young Lawyers Section Executive\nCommittee and past chairpersons of the Section are not eligible for nomination.\n• All submissions require a completed nomination form. Please attach additional sheets,\nif necessary.\n• Letters and a resume supporting the nomination will be considered, if they enhance the\ninformation provided in the nomination form', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4195, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11562, 135, 'http://www.njbiz.com/', 'Business of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.njbiz.com/section/Business-of-the-Year-Nom', '', 0, '2015-09-10', 2, 'The NJBIZ Business of the Year awards recognizes the state’s most dynamic businesses and business leaders who share a commitment to professional excellence, business growth and the community. Award Categories:\n- Business of the Year (1-50 employees)\n- Business of the Year (51-100 employees)\n- Business of the Year (101+ employees)\n- Corporate Citizen of the Year\n- Emerging Business of the Year\n\nEligibility:\n- Nominees may not be entered in a category in which they have previously won. After a five year period, companies may re-apply for a category in which they have already won.\n- Nominees may be self-nominated or nominated by someone else.\n- Nominees may only be entered in one category.\n- Nominees may not be members of the judges’ panel or members of the judges’ families.\n- Nominations that do not follow guidelines may be subject to disqualification. \n- Past finalists will be accepted.', 0, 0, 'Law Firm; Organization; Company', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4196, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11563, 135, 'http://www.njbiz.com/', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'http://www.bestplacestoworkinnj.com/index.php?option=com_frontpage&Itemid=1', '', 0, '2015-11-13', 2, 'Eligibility\nTo be eligible for consideration, companies must meet the following criteria:\nBe a for-profit or not-for-profit business or government entity\nBe a publicly or privately held business\nHave a facility in the state of New Jersey\nHave a minimum of 15 employees working in the state of New Jersey*\nMust be in business a minimum of 1 year\n*To ensure the credibility of the information, companies with 15-24 employees must have an 80% (or better) response rate to be considered for the list.', 0, 0, 'Law Firm; Organization; Company', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4197, 'subscribed', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11564, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Business Women First', 2016, '', '', 0, '2015-12-18', 14, 'Presented by the Pittsburgh Business Times, the  BusinessWomen First Awards honor the region''s most influential business women at both for-profits and non-profits. We''re looking for women from every industry and profession; women who''ve made a difference in their communities, blazed a trail for other women and are leaving a mark on the western Pennsylvania business community.\nNominees must be female residents of western Pennsylvania who are employed in the region.\nA nominee should be an established business leader with a strong record of innovation in her field with outstanding performance in her business or non-profit or organization.\nNominations should include as much detail as possible about a nominee''s specific business accomplishments. We''re looking for real tangible results, as in ''She increased the company''s sales last year by 40%, bringing in AOL and Nextel as clients.''\nNominees do not have to be the owners or presidents of their organizations. We do not publicize the name of the person who enters a nomination.\nNominees will be judged on their role as business or non-profit leaders. We''re looking for entrepreneurs and executives whose efforts are molding their workplace and their industry.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4198, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11565, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Family Business Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77472', '', 0, '2016-02-12', 14, ' Presented by the Pittsburgh Business Times, the 2016 Family Business Awards will honor multi-generational, family-owned businesses in our region for overall excellence, innovation, ethics and philanthropy. Finalists will be selected by an independent panel of judges.\nCompanies who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016.\nFinalists will be announced in advance. Winners will be named at a luncheon during the second week of May of 2016. Finalists and winners will be honored in a special supplement to the Pittsburgh Business Times on May 13, 2016\n.\nAwards will be presented in categories based on employee count.', 0, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4199, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11566, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Energy Leadership Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77482#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-02-19', 14, 'The 2016 Energy Leadership Awards honor individuals for outstanding contributions to western Pennsylvania''s energy sector.\n\nWe honor all types of energy leadership  – from energy companies that explore and drill for gas and oil to the attorneys and accountants who supply services to them. While natural gas is clearly a strong focal point of the program, the 2016 Energy Leadership Awards will honor all categories, including natural gas, oil, coal, nuclear, wind and solar. If you work with the energy industry or know a person who does, you should consider entering the 2016 Energy Leadership Awards.\n\nThis is the sixth year for the program, which includes an awards event and a special supplement in May of 2016.\n\nWinners will be announced in May of 2016 at the Energy Gala, a reception honoring the region''s energy leaders.', 0, 0, 'Community or Civic', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4200, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11567, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Fast Trackers', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77502#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-03-11', 14, 'Fast Trackers honors leaders in Pittsburgh''s business and nonprofit communities who are under 40 years old as of June 1, 2016. Winners are selected for their successful efforts to grow a business or nonprofit. Fast Trackers don''t have to be owners, presidents or executive directors of their organizations, but they must have shown to have had a significant impact on the growth, scope or impact of the organization.\nSelf-nominations are encouraged for this program. Individuals who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016. Winners are in a special Business Times supplement and through online coverage.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4201, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11568, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Healthiest Employers in Western Pennsylvania', 2016, 'http://healthiestemployers.com/portfolio/western-pennsylvania/', '', 0, '2016-03-11', 14, 'The 2016 Healthiest Employers in Western Pennsylvania awards program honors companies in Western Pennsylvania for programs developed to improve the health and wellness of employees. To participate, a company representitive must register on this website.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4202, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11569, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Fastest Growing Companies', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77522#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-05-20', 14, 'Do you represent one of our region''s fastest-growing companies? You should enter the 2016 Pittsburgh 100.\nTo qualify, companies must be locally owned, for-profit corporations, proprietorships or partnerships. Revenue growth is ranked over a three-year period between 2013 and 2015. Gross revenue in 2013 must be $500,000 or above. Some information, including the percentage of growth between 2013 and 2015, will be included in the Pittsburgh 100 supplement of the Pittsburgh Business Times in August of 2016. Revenue numbers are not published as part of this List, but may be used for and published in other Lists, such as the Largest Regional Private Companies. If you do not want your revenue figures published in any Lists, please contact Ethan Lott, elott@bizjournals.com or 412-208-3823.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4203, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
