(11570, 136, 'www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77542#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-05-27', 14, 'The 2016 Best Places to Work in Western Pennsylvania honors the region''s most outstanding workplaces. Winners are selected based on an online employee survey in June of this year and are honored at an event and in a special supplement. You must have at least 10 employees working in western Pennsylvania to participate. (Anyone with 5 percent or more ownership in the company may not participate in the survey and does not count toward the final employee total.) Companies do not have to be based in western Pennsylvania. Only employees working in the region are included in the survey and results. You''ll be notified in late May, 2016, with instructions on how to sign up for the online survey.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4204, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11571, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Women in Energy Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77532#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-05-27', 14, 'The 2016 Health Care Heroes Awards will honor the individuals, companies and organizations in western Pennsylvania for their contributions to improving health care in our region. Awards are presented in seven categories: Community Outreach, Health Care Innovation, Health Care Provider - Physician, Health Care Provider - Nonphysician, Volunteer, Health Care Executive and Lifetime Achievement.The selections are made by an independent panel of judges. Winners and finalists are honored at an event and in a special supplement in September of 2016.\nSelf-nominations are encouraged. The names of the nominators are not publicized at any stage of this program.\nIndividuals who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4205, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11572, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Healthcare Hero Awards', 2016, 'http://healthiestemployers.com/portfolio/western-pennsylvania/', '', 0, '2016-06-10', 14, 'The 2016 Health Care Heroes Awards will honor the individuals, companies and organizations in western Pennsylvania for their contributions to improving health care in our region. Awards are presented in seven categories: Community Outreach, Health Care Innovation, Health Care Provider - Physician, Health Care Provider - Nonphysician, Volunteer, Health Care Executive and Lifetime Achievement.The selections are made by an independent panel of judges. Winners and finalists are honored at an event and in a special supplement in September of 2016.\nSelf-nominations are encouraged. The names of the nominators are not publicized at any stage of this program.\nIndividuals who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4206, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11573, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Who''s Who In Energy', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/78082#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-08-12', 14, 'With the Pittsburgh region becoming an energy bastion in the east, help us identify the movers and shakers fueling the energy boom in our region.\n\nThis fall, the Pittsburgh Business Times will publish the fourth annual edition of a multistate publication, ''Who''s Who in Energy.''\n\nBusiness journals in five cities - Dallas, Denver, Houston, Pittsburgh and San Antonio - will partner on this undertaking, the result of which will be a listing of some 700 business leaders across sectors and states who are shaping today''s ever-evolving energy market.\n\nThe Pittsburgh Business Times will accept nominations through Aug. 12, 2016. Honorees can work in positions throughout the energy industry, including (but not limited to) finance, law, engineering, renewable, manufacturing, advocacy/education/training and energy companies themselves.\n\nYou can nominate yourself or another outstanding Pittsburgh regional business leader.\n\nThe Business Times will vet all entries and make the final decision on this year''s movers and shakers.\n\nVisit the other business journal sites to nominate individuals in those markets.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4207, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11574, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'CFO of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77552#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-08-19', 14, 'The CFO of the Year Awards honors financial professionals in western Pennsylvania for outstanding performance as corporate financial stewards.\n\nEligibility: Nominees must be Chief Financial Officers or hold equivalent positions in the western Pennsylvania region. Companies do not have to be headquartered in region, but CFO nominees must have home office in the region.\n\nIndividuals who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016.\nAwards\nAwards will be provided in categories. Up to five finalists will be selected in each category. Winners will be announced at the awards ceremony. Categories include:\n• Public\n• Non-Profit\n• Private (three categories based on company size using employee count)\n• Lifetime Achievement (new for 2016)\nRecognition: Finalists and winners will be honored at a dinner awards ceremony in November, 2016 at the Omni William Penn Hotel in downtown Pittsburgh. A special supplement honoring participants will be inserted in the Pittsburgh Business Times later that same week.\nSelection Process: An independent panel of judges, which includes winners of the 2015 CFO of the Year Awards will select winners based on information provided through this online nomination. Only online nominations will be accepted.\nSpecial Notes:\n• Self-nominations account for more than half of all nominations for awards programs presented by the Pittsburgh Business Times. We do not publicize the nominator in any way. Judges are not provided with the names or affiliations of nominators. They review only the answers to the questions from this nomination.\n• This system does not save your nomination. We recommend that you first draft your responses in a Word document in the event you either experience an error message or want to review the nomination in the future. Do not exceed 2,000 characters, including spaces, per field.\nIf you want to nominate someone, but don''t have the information to complete this form\nIf you know of a deserving candidate for this award, but don''t feel you have the necessary information to complete the nomination:\n1. Provide your name and contact information.\n2. Provide the nominee''s name and contact information.\n3. Put ''NA'' in the remaining fields. You''ll be contacted about someone from the Business Times reaching out to the candidate to get the rest of the information.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4208, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11575, 136, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/', 'Manufacturer of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/nomination/77562#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-09-02', 14, 'The 2016 Manufacturer of the Year Awards are given to companies based on information provided in this online nomination form by a panel of independent judges. There are three award categories: Overall, Sustainable and a category that was introduced last year - the Family Business Award.\nNote: Companies who won this award in 2015 are not eligible to participate in 2016.\nOverall\nUp to five finalists and one winner are selected in three overall categories based on employee count (small, medium, large).\nSustainable\nThe sustainable manufacturing award is based on sustainable products or processes at a manufacturing facility in western Pennsylvania. Up to five finalists and one winner are selected in the sustainable category.\n\nPremo J. Pappafava Family Business Award\nThis award will recognize multi-generational, family-owned manufacturers for overall excellence, innovation, ethics and philanthropy. One winner is selected in this category.\n\nSelf-nominations are encouraged for this program. Nearly all finalists and winners from prior years were the result of nominations by someone at the company.\n\nYou may apply for both the overall or sustainable award, or for only the sustainable or overall category.\n\nThis nominating system does not save your work. We suggest you provide the narratives to the questions on this form in a Word document, then copy them into the answer fields.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4209, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11576, 137, 'http://www.powermag.com/power-awards/', 'Power Awards - Plant of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.powermag.com/', 'Power;', 0, '2016-04-29', 0, 'For over four decades, POWER magazine has honored the top performers in the electricity-generating industry with annual power plant awards. If your plant has distinguished itself by innovative design or engineering upgrades, producing power more reliably or economically than comparable plants, or demonstrating a new generation or environmental controls technology, don’t miss the opportunity to see your plant profiled in POWER. We also offer an award for a noteworthy smart grid project and plant water-related project.\n\nAward winners will be selected by the editors of POWER based on nominations submitted by you and your industry peers—suppliers, designers, constructors, and operators of power plants. Don’t be shy about nominating your plant; most of our past winners were nominated by plant staff. If your project is selected as an award finalist, a POWER editor will contact you to develop an article that will be published in POWER to inform the rest of the industry of your achievement. Additionally, all winners will be mailed an award that displays their project’s name on a custom POWER cover. Plant of the Year\n\nThe Plant of the Year award is given to a power plant that leads our industry in the successful deployment of advanced technology and maximizing efficiency while minimizing environmental impact. Historically, this award has been presented to a plant that entered commercial service within the past one to two years. The Plant of the Year will be profiled in the August issue of POWER', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4210, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11577, 137, 'http://www.powermag.com/power-awards/', 'Power Awards - Reinvention Award (previously Marmaduke Award)', 2016, 'http://www.powermag.com/', 'Power;', 0, '2016-04-29', 0, 'For over four decades, POWER magazine has honored the top performers in the electricity-generating industry with annual power plant awards. If your plant has distinguished itself by innovative design or engineering upgrades, producing power more reliably or economically than comparable plants, or demonstrating a new generation or environmental controls technology, don’t miss the opportunity to see your plant profiled in POWER. We also offer an award for a noteworthy smart grid project and plant water-related project.\n\nAward winners will be selected by the editors of POWER based on nominations submitted by you and your industry peers—suppliers, designers, constructors, and operators of power plants. Don’t be shy about nominating your plant; most of our past winners were nominated by plant staff. If your project is selected as an award finalist, a POWER editor will contact you to develop an article that will be published in POWER to inform the rest of the industry of your achievement. Additionally, all winners will be mailed an award that displays their project’s name on a custom POWER cover. Reinvention Award (previously Marmaduke Award)\n\nThe Reinvention Award recognizes excellence in creative problem-solving that gives a power plant of any type a new life or a new role. Prior winners include an operating combined cycle plant that was moved from one multi-unit plant to another multi-unit plant, a coal-fired plant that was repowered with a circulating fluidized bed (CFB) boiler burning wood, and a district heating plant that was repowered with new, high-efficiency gas turbines. The Reinvention Award winner will be profiled in the August issue of POWER.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4211, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11578, 137, 'http://www.powermag.com/power-awards/', 'Power Awards - Smart Grid Award', 2016, 'http://www.powermag.com/', 'Power;', 0, '2016-04-29', 0, 'For over four decades, POWER magazine has honored the top performers in the electricity-generating industry with annual power plant awards. If your plant has distinguished itself by innovative design or engineering upgrades, producing power more reliably or economically than comparable plants, or demonstrating a new generation or environmental controls technology, don’t miss the opportunity to see your plant profiled in POWER. We also offer an award for a noteworthy smart grid project and plant water-related project.\n\nAward winners will be selected by the editors of POWER based on nominations submitted by you and your industry peers—suppliers, designers, constructors, and operators of power plants. Don’t be shy about nominating your plant; most of our past winners were nominated by plant staff. If your project is selected as an award finalist, a POWER editor will contact you to develop an article that will be published in POWER to inform the rest of the industry of your achievement. Additionally, all winners will be mailed an award that displays their project’s name on a custom POWER cover. Smart Grid Award\n\n2011 was the inaugural year for the POWER Smart Grid Award. Although the magazine has traditionally focused on the supply end of the power industry, the business and technology of power generation is becoming increasingly affected by smart grid developments that touch the entire power supply and delivery chain. This award recognizes an outstanding smart grid project, anywhere in the world, of any scale, that demonstrates the benefits of new data-rich technologies to power generators, distribution utilities, and customers. Specifically, we are looking for nominations of projects that are:\n\nUpstream of smart meters and home energy management or automation devices, so no automated meter reading or advanced metering infrastructure projects, please—unless they are just a portion of a more comprehensive smart grid project that has several other non-end-user components.\nClearly “smart”—that integrate information and communications technology-assisted components that represent more than maintenance-level improvement.\nSetting a new standard for quality and results. Being the “first” or “largest” or “cheapest” of a given type of project will be noted but will not be the weightiest criterion. Whether large or small, the winning project will need to demonstrate achievement in technology and service that is worthy of being considered a best practice.\nAble to demonstrate material results from at least six months of operation prior to the nomination deadline. No planned or in-progress projects, please. (We realize that all true smart grid projects are works in progress, but we are looking for projects with a defined scope that have been completed, monitored, and reported on.) For example, specify costs saved by end users, outages averted that would not previously have been avoided, dispatchable or controllable small-scale distributed generation resources added to the grid in such a way that they strengthen the grid rather than destabilize it, or some other metric(s) that illustrate the substantive benefits enjoyed by one or (preferably) more grid stakeholders.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4212, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11579, 137, 'http://www.powermag.com/power-awards/', 'Power Awards - Top Plants', 2016, 'http://www.powermag.com/', 'Power;', 0, '2016-04-29', 0, 'For over four decades, POWER magazine has honored the top performers in the electricity-generating industry with annual power plant awards. If your plant has distinguished itself by innovative design or engineering upgrades, producing power more reliably or economically than comparable plants, or demonstrating a new generation or environmental controls technology, don’t miss the opportunity to see your plant profiled in POWER. We also offer an award for a noteworthy smart grid project and plant water-related project.\n\nAward winners will be selected by the editors of POWER based on nominations submitted by you and your industry peers—suppliers, designers, constructors, and operators of power plants. Don’t be shy about nominating your plant; most of our past winners were nominated by plant staff. If your project is selected as an award finalist, a POWER editor will contact you to develop an article that will be published in POWER to inform the rest of the industry of your achievement. Additionally, all winners will be mailed an award that displays their project’s name on a custom POWER cover. Top Plants\n\nTop Plant winners are profiled annually in these issues of POWER:\n\nNatural gas-fired projects in September\nCoal-fired projects in October\nNuclear projects in November\nRenewable projects in December\nTop Plants are interesting, important, innovative projects. Many Top Plants are recently commissioned facilities that exhibit some unique design or technology that will be of general interest to the power industry. They also can include plants that have distinguished themselves as industry leaders for significant improvements made to their equipment, operations, staffing, or operating record to emerge from an “also ran” to top of the class in performance.', 0, 0, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4213, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11580, 137, '', 'Power Awards - Water Award', 2016, '', 'Community or Civic', 2015, '1970-01-01', 0, 'For over four decades, POWER magazine has honored the top performers in the electricity-generating industry with annual power plant awards. If your plant has distinguished itself by innovative design or engineering upgrades, producing power more reliably or economically than comparable plants, or demonstrating a new generation or environmental controls technology, don’t miss the opportunity to see your plant profiled in POWER. We also offer an award for a noteworthy smart grid project and plant water-related project.\n\nAward winners will be selected by the editors of POWER based on nominations submitted by you and your industry peers—suppliers, designers, constructors, and operators of power plants. Don’t be shy about nominating your plant; most of our past winners were nominated by plant staff. If your project is selected as an award finalist, a POWER editor will contact you to develop an article that will be published in POWER to inform the rest of the industry of your achievement. Additionally, all winners will be mailed an award that displays their project’s name on a custom POWER cover. Water Award\n\nIntroduced in 2014, the Water Award goes to a water-related project at a power plant anywhere in the world that demonstrates leadership in the management of water and/or wastewater streams. Winning projects will have successfully implemented innovative, leading-edge approaches to water stewardship, water quality, water availability, or wastewater-handling issues. Although technology may be involved, the award is not specifically for a new commercially available technology. Rather, the award recognizes creative problem-solving that results in water management strategies that may serve as models for other plants. ''|29-Apr-16|0|0|||USA''', 0, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4214, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11581, 138, '', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/nomination', '', 0, '2016-03-25', 3, 'The San Antonio Business Journal is seeking nominations for its Best Places to Work awards. To nominate, companies must complete this form below and register for their employees to complete an electronic survey. The deadline to submit nominations is March 25.', 0, 0, 'Law Firm; Company; Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4215, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11582, 138, '', 'Outstanding Lawyer Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/nomination', '', 0, '2016-06-10', 3, 'The San Antonio Business Journal''s Outstanding Lawyer Awards recognize lawyers in our community who are making a difference in their organizations, the legal industry and the community.\n\nNominees must be practicing lawyers who have passed the Texas Bar exam and are current on continuing professional education requirements.\nThe nominee’s home office must be in the San Antonio area.\n ', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11583, 139, '', 'Residential Real Estate Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/nomination', '', 0, '2016-02-25', 3, 'The San Antonio Business Journal is seeking nominations for the Top Residential Real Agents in the following categories: Luxury Real Estate Agents, Luxury Real Estate Teams, Individual Agents, Residential Real Estate Teams, and Farm & Ranch Agents', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11584, 139, '', 'Best in Commercial Real Estate - Heavy Hitters', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-04-01', 767, 'The San Antonio Business Journal invites you to nominate San Antonio-based brokers for its 2016 Commercial Real EstateHeavy Hitters Awards. Nominated brokers must be involved in commercial real estate transactions in Bexar, Comal, Guadalupe, Kendall, Wilson, Atascosa, Bandera or Medina county. And sales figures must reflect only transactions in that eight-county area.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11585, 139, '', 'Women''s Leadership Awards', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/nomination', '', 0, '2016-06-24', 3, '', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4216, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11586, 140, '', 'Barrister of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'The entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of one benchmark case, illustrating how the individual barrister’s contribution made a significant difference to the outcome, including details of other parties / instructing groups\nInformation relating to previous career history including:\nKey cases\nInitiatives undertaken outside of the law\nSupporting testimony from Private Practice colleagues', 0, 1, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4217, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11587, 140, '', 'Boutique Firm of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'This category is open to specialist or regional firms from across the UK which focus primarily on one practice area; entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nEvidence of:\nStrategic vision and strong leadership\nStrong financial management and growth\nInnovation in client service delivery \nInnovation in pricing\nExcellent talent management and workplace development\nKey clients\nSignificant client wins and feedback\nRecent hires and investment\nLeadership team (including biographies)\nYou will also be asked to provide details of up to three cases or transactions which demonstrate:\nExcellence in the firm’s chosen field\nDepth and breadth of expertise\nCommercial strength\nMarket share and evidence of both growth and retention within their client list\nLegal and/or entrepreneurial innovation\nEvidence of market leading strategy', 0, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4218, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11588, 140, '', 'Chambers of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'The entry form will ask you for:\nDetails of up to five cases which demonstrate:\nDepth and breadth of quality of work undertaken\nExpertise within a specific area(s)\nGrowth and response to market shifts\nInnovative management and clerking\nYou will also be asked to provide details of: \nYear on year growth in business activity\nFinancial performance\nClearly identifiable strategy\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nOutcomes and precedents set', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department; Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4219, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11589, 140, '', 'Client Partner of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'This year The Lawyer will be going out to its top in-house contacts to gather nominations for Client Partner of the Year; these nominations will be supplemented by information taken from our research portal The Lawyer Market Intelligence.\nFactors taken into account will include:\nSignificant work undertaken by the Partner\nEvidence of innovation and problem solving skills demonstrated by the Partner\nThe Partner’s understanding of the client’s business, company culture and sector\nHow well embedded into the client company the Partner has become, and the levels of interaction between the Partner and senior business executives\nIf you would like to make any recommendations to the panel regarding who should be nominated, please email the following items to sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com:\nYour name and contact details\nName and contact details (where possible) of the nominee\n300 word statement (max) detailing why this person should win, taking into account the above factors', 0, 1, 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4220, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11590, 140, '', 'Competition Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set for contentious work\n\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.   ', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4221, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11591, 140, '', 'Corporate Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout transaction from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThis category is open to transactional teams. We are looking for excellence in one of the following fields: IPO’s (main list or AIM), public M&A, private equity or corporate reorganisations. Entries are welcomed from both domestic and cross-border work. \n\nThe entry form will ask you for:\n\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\n\nEvidence of what makes this deal truly unique and challenging\n\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\n\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\n\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4222, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11592, 140, '', 'Employment Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter heard in England and Wales in which judgment was delivered after 1 April 2015.\nAlthough we recognise that it is always preferable to engage in mediation or dispute resolution, this category can only recognise cases that are on public record. The category is open to lawyers specialising in insurance, reinsurance, construction, tax & trusts, defamation, as well as general commercial litigation.\nOngoing cases will not be considered.\nAlthough we welcome entries which are being heard across multiple jurisdictions, a material element of the case must have been heard in the High Court or Appellate Courts of England and Wales. \n The entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen case including:\nMarket context\nFull list of representation\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4223, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11593, 140, '', 'Energy Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries for this category should focus on one standout transaction completed between 1st April 2015 and the present time. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of the client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4224, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
