(11604, 140, '', 'Infrastructure Projects Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout transaction from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThis category is open to firms involved in international projects as well as UK PPP and PFI work.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nSensitivity to political/local considerations\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4235, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11605, 140, '', 'International Firm of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'This category is open to international firms operating globally across any number of jurisdictions; this year we also encourage entries from teams based in the Asia offices of UK or international firms. Entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nDetails of up to five cases / deals which demonstrate:\nClear market-leading strategic vision for the region \nDepth and breadth of expertise\nConsistent delivery of client service\nCommercial strength\nMarket share and evidence of both growth and retention within their client list\nLegal and/or entrepreneurial innovation\nA list of key clients and local client wins\nAny other information which demonstrates progress made throughout the year, for example:\nYear on year growth in business activity\nFinancial performance\nClearly identifiable strategy\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nKey hires and investment', 0, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4236, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11606, 140, '', 'IP Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThis category includes IP and data protection rights as well as IT and Telecoms. The entries may be contentious as well as non-contentious. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4237, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11607, 140, '', 'Law Firm of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'This category is open to any firm headquartered in the UK; entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nEntries will not be judged on organisational size and turnover alone, but on the clarity of the strategic vision demonstrated.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nEvidence of:\nStrategic vision and strong leadership\nStrong financial management and growth\nInnovation in client service delivery \nInnovation in pricing\nExcellence in their chosen sector(s)\nExcellent talent management and workplace development\nSignificant client wins and feedback\nRecent hires and investment\nLeadership team brief (including biographies)', 0, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4238, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11608, 140, '', 'Litigation Team of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter heard in England and Wales in which judgment was delivered after 1 April 2015.\nAlthough we recognise that it is always preferable to engage in mediation or dispute resolution, this category can only recognise cases that are on public record. The category is open to lawyers specialising in insurance, reinsurance, construction, tax & trusts, defamation, as well as general commercial litigation.\nOngoing cases will not be considered.\nAlthough we welcome entries which are being heard across multiple jurisdictions, a material element of the case must have been heard in the High Court or Appellate Courts of England and Wales. \n The entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen case including:\nMarket context\nFull list of representation\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4239, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11609, 140, '', 'Offshore Firm of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'The entry form will ask you for:\nInformation that demonstrates:\nExcellence in your key jurisdiction\nDepth and breadth of expertise\nCommercial strength, including financial results\nMarket share and evidence of both growth and retention within your client list\nLegal and/or entrepreneurial innovation\nEvidence of market-leading strategy', 0, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4240, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11610, 140, '', 'Pro Bono Initiative of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries should include details of a lead piece of pro bono work.\nPlease provide evidence of:\na. Innovative thinking\nb. Senior buy-in from across the organisation\nc. Measurable outcomes and how the project generated significant change\nWhere possible please provide testimonials from relevant parties\nPlease provide details of any supporting pro bono work.', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department; Practice Group', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4241, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
