(11611, 140, '', 'Real Estate Team of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.thelawyerawards.com/categories', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter from 1st April 2015 until the present time. Real estate team of the year is open to commercial property lawyers working in the planning, development, finance or institutional investment arenas. The entry form will ask you for: Full details of the chosen deal including: Market context History of client relationship History of representation – did the representation change? Technical innovation Innovation in client service Innovation in pricing Measurable outcomes A list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel. Supporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of: Innovation in pricing and service delivery Client wins Political sensitivity Financial performance Consistently excellent project management skills Outcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve Precedents set Multiple entries from one firm are acceptable.', 0, 1, 'Law Firm; Legal Department; Practice Group', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4242, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11612, 140, '', 'Regional Firm of the Year', 2016, '', '', 0, '2016-03-04', 10, 'This category is open to any firm headquartered in the UK outside of London; entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nEntries will not be judged on organisational size and turnover alone, but on the clarity of the strategic vision demonstrated.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nEvidence of:\nStrategic vision and strong leadership\nStrong financial management and growth\nInnovation in client service delivery \nInnovation in pricing\nExcellence in their chosen sector(s)\nExcellent talent management and workplace development\nSignificant client wins and feedback\nRecent hires and investment\nLeadership team brief (including biographies)\nAn outline of the particular challenges faced by the firm and its peers in current market conditions, and explain how these challenges have been overcome.', 0, 1, 'Law Firm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4243, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11613, 141, '', '25 Influential Black Women in Business', 2016, 'http://www.tnj.com/25-Influential-black-women/2015', '', 0, '2016-02-05', 2, 'Launched in March 1999, The Network Journal''s 25 Influential Black Women in Business Awards honors women whose professional achievements have significantly impacted an industry or profession, and who also have made an important contribution to their community. A ''TNJ25'' honoree typically is a business owner, or a partner, president, CEO, board chair, or other senior-management executive with significant decision-making authority in the corporate, nonprofit (including academia and medicine), or government sector.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11614, 141, '', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'http://www.tnj.com/40-under-forty/call-for-nominations', '', 0, '2016-02-05', 2, 'THE SEARCH IS ON. We are searching for the most dynamic business and professional leaders under the age of 40. We''re looking for candidates who share a commitment to business growth and professional excellence and to the community.\n \nThe 19th Annual 40 Under Forty Achievement Awards will honor this new generation of men and women who are making headlines in their fields. Winners will be featured in the special issue of The Network Journal, June 2016. Anyone who is 39 years or younger on or before June 15, 2016 is eligible.', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11615, 142, '', 'CFO of the Year', 2016, 'http://www.bizjournals.com/washington/nomination/79622#eligibility', '', 0, '2016-04-29', 14, 'This award honors the region''s top financial professionals in Greater Washington for outstanding performance in their roles as corporate financial stewards.  Nominees should be either a chief financial officer or hold an equivalent position at a company or organization based in D.C. or one of the following jurisdictions: Alexandria, Arlington, Fairfax, Prince William and Loudoun counties in Virginia and Prince George''s and Montgomery counties in Maryland. ', 0, 0, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '', '', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
