(151, 'Chambers & Partners', 'Dispute Resolution', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the worldChambers'' Dispute Resolution and Litigation coverage includes the full course of a dispute such as pre-trial negotiations, documentation and preparation for trial, summary judgement motions, trial, appeals and enforcement proceedings. There are two main types of litigation: commercial disputes before civil courts, and white-collar crime, including government investigations. Alternative dispute resolution, involving non-court mediation is also featured. Many commercial contracts contain arbitration clauses, which are handled by commercial litigators. In the larger markets, such as the UK and the USA, we will also produce standalone ranking tables. The USA coverage focuses on commercial proceedings before state and federal court, circuit courts and US Supreme Court. In the some countries, the practice of litigation is sufficiently specialised for Chambers to identify specialists. Areas such as Insurance, Construction, Environment IP and Media all contain litigators who are experts in their field.   Please note that the area of Dispute Resolution contains the following subsections: Litigation, Arbitration, Most in Demand Arbitrators.', '23-Feb-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'Austria', 'Europe', 'Litigation', '', 'Annual', 'Graham Gilbert', 'GrahamGilbert@Chambersandpartners.co.uk', '+4420 7778 1632', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
