(202, 'Chambers & Partners', 'Shipping', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the world.Shipping & maritime litigation involves breach of charter-party disputes, cargo and bills of lading claims, the arrest of vessels and cargoes, marine insurance claims, collision, salvage and environmental liabilities. On the non-contentious side, law firms advise on contractual arrangements for construction, financing and registration of vessels, customs and licensing, and documentation relating to charter-parties and bills of lading.', '29-Feb-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'Bangladesh', 'Asia', 'Transportation', 'Shipping', 'Annual', 'Georgina Gittens', 'GeorginaGittens@Chambersandpartners.co.uk', '+4420 7778 1672', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
