(264, 'Chambers & Partners', 'Banking & Finance', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the worldA broad-based definition of banking transactions, which include advice to both borrower and lender clients. The following topics are included:\n\nAcquisition finance: transactions involving arranging finance for acquisitions acting for either the lender or the borrower.\n\nIslamic Finance: Sharia-compliant work such as acquisitions, forming funds to invest in real estate and commercial properties, issuing of Sukuks.\n\nGeneral bank lending: syndicated lending, structured finance, leveraged finance.\n\nProject finance: financing of infrastructure and industrial projects. Often arranged on a non-recourse loan basis. See also equipment finance and leasing.\n\nRefinancing: The refinancing and restructuring of existing loans and debtor in possession financing is also included.    This section includes Banking & Finance: Capital Markets. Please include any Capital Markets work as part of the main Banking & Finance submission, Any relevant clients should also be part of the list of 10 Banking & Finance referees.', '1-Mar-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'Colombia', 'South America', 'Banking & Finance', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
