(483, 'Chambers & Partners', 'Healthcare (PRC Firms)', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the world.Life Sciences focuses on the commercialisation of life sciences products (pharmaceuticals, medical devices and biotechnology programs etc). IP issues dominate as large pharmaceuticals seek to obtain innovative, impending blockbuster drugs from biotechs and other pharmaceutical companies. Also includes the licensing and acquisition of new products from other sources (often smaller biotechs to larger suppliers). This chapter includes advice on FDA issues and the increased focus on drug and device safety, which also appears in our Healthcare and Life Sciences coverage.', '27-Jun-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'China', 'Asia', 'Life Sciences', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', '', '', ''),
(484, 'Chambers & Partners', 'Shipping (PRC Firms)', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the world.Shipping & maritime litigation involves breach of charter-party disputes, cargo and bills of lading claims, the arrest of vessels and cargoes, marine insurance claims, collision, salvage and environmental liabilities. On the non-contentious side, law firms advise on contractual arrangements for construction, financing and registration of vessels, customs and licensing, and documentation relating to charter-parties and bills of lading.', '27-Jun-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'China', 'Asia', 'Transportation', 'Shipping; PRC;', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
