(588, 'Chambers & Partners', 'International Trade/WTO', 2016, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the worldChambers'' Dispute Resolution and Litigation coverage includes the full course of a dispute such as pre-trial negotiations, documentation and preparation for trial, summary judgement motions, trial, appeals and enforcement proceedings. There are two main types of litigation: commercial disputes before civil courts, and white-collar crime, including government investigations. Alternative dispute resolution, involving non-court mediation is also featured. Many commercial contracts contain arbitration clauses, which are handled by commercial litigators. In the larger markets, such as the UK and the USA, we will also produce standalone ranking tables. The USA coverage focuses on commercial proceedings before state and federal court, circuit courts and US Supreme Court. In the some countries, the practice of litigation is sufficiently specialised for Chambers to identify specialists. Areas such as Insurance, Construction, Environment IP and Media all contain litigators who are experts in their field.', '7-Nov-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'Colombia', 'South America', 'International Trade', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
(589, 'Chambers & Partners ', 'Banking & Finance', 2015, 'The Chambers Guides have been ranking the best law firms and lawyers since 1990, and now cover 185 jurisdictions throughout the world. A broad-based definition of banking transactions, which include advice to both borrower and lender clients. The following topics are included: Acquisition finance: transactions involving arranging finance for acquisitions acting for either the lender or the borrower. Islamic Finance: Sharia-compliant work such as acquisitions, forming funds to invest in real estate and commercial properties, issuing of Sukuks. General bank lending: syndicated lending, structured finance, leveraged finance. Project finance: financing of infrastructure and industrial projects. Often arranged on a non-recourse loan basis. See also equipment finance and leasing. Refinancing: The refinancing and restructuring of existing loans and debtor in possession financing is also included.', '2-Nov-15', 1, 1, '', '', 'Guatemala', 'North America', 'Banking & Finance', '', 'Annual', 'Carlota GarciaPatel', '', '4420 7778 1643', 'Law Firm; Practice Group', '', '', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/global-practice-area-definitions', 'http://www.chambersandpartners.com/', ''),
