(603, 'Charlotte Business Journal', 'CIO of the Year Awards', 2016, 'Technology is an integral part of doing business. Utilizing it to proactively advance company initiatives takes strategy, planning and implementation.\nThe Charlotte Business Journal''s 2016 CIO of the Year Awards is the premier technology executive recognition program for the Greater Charlotte region. The Awards honor IT executives and emerging leaders who have shown excellence in leading information technology. The awards will recognize the top technology executive in companies that used IT in innovative ways to create a competitive advantage, optimize business processes, enable company growth and impact the company''s bottom line.', '8-May-16', 0, 0, 'Charlotte', 'NC', 'USA', 'US South', '', 'Recognition: Honorees and winners will be recognized at an awards program and in a special publication of the Charlotte Business Journal on November 2014.\n    Free Survey Overview Report: You will get a free report on your company''s survey results, which ', 'Annual', 'Allie Gatlin', 'agatlin@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte/nomination/79482#eligibility', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/charlotte', ''),
(604, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'Fast 55 Awards', 2016, 'The Business Courier needs your help in identifying Greater Cincinnati''s fastest-growing companies. To be eligible for Fast 55, a company must:\nbe independent, for-profit and privately held;\nbe headquartered in the 17-county, three-state Greater Cincinnati region;\nhave a three-year operating history;\nhave an average of at least $1 million in sales for the three most recent years, with no year less than $200,000.', '29-Feb-16', 0, 1, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(605, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'C-Suite Awards', 2016, 'The C-Suite Awards recognizes Greater Cincinnati''s top executives for their contribution and commitment to the community and their outstanding professional performance.', '6-May-16', 0, 1, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(606, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'Young professionals are a vital asset to our region and it is important to acknowledge those who are making great strides in shaping our community''s future. Since 1995, the Business Courier has recognized our region''s young talent through our annual Forty Under 40 awards.\nEach year through our open nominations process, we seek forty individuals, under the age of 40, who are making a difference in business and community. The emphasis is on leadership and potential leadership- whether it is in business, politics, the arts, nonprofits, education, health care or public service. Focus is also placed on the nominee''s community involvement. Think of your friends, family, colleagues, clients -- anyone who matches the criteria -- and nominate as many as you''d like.', '3-Jun-16', 0, 0, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Age', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(607, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'Second Act Awards', 2016, 'The days of working for a single company for your entire life are over. Many are starting fresh, either joining existing companies with a new career or starting their own challenge. \nThe Business Courier is proud to announce the Second Act awards, honoring Cincinnatians who have found success after a first career, as either owner or manager. \nThe target age for our honorees will be at, near, or above 60 years.\nAll nominees must be residents of the 17-county, three state Greater Cincinnati region. These counties include: Ohio - Brown, Butler, Clermont, Clinton, Hamilton, Highland and Warren; Kentucky - Boone, Bracken, Campbell, Gallatin, Grant, Kenton, and Pendleton; Indiana - Dearborn, Franklin, and Ohio.   ', '3-Jun-16', 0, 0, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Age', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(608, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'Outstanding Board Excellence', 2016, 'During the nomination and selection process we heard from many CEO’s and owners that they felt it was not fair for them to nominate only one board member so after discussion we have decided to add a category for “Board Excellence”. This award will take into consideration your entire outside board of directors. It will be a group award and will focus on two qualifying questions;\n\nWhat distinguishes your board’s accomplishments from those of its peers\nWhat impact has your board had on the company or organization', '15-Jul-16', 0, 0, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(609, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'Outstanding Director Awards', 2016, 'The 2016 Outstanding Director Awards will honor directors who have significantly influenced boardroom practices and performance; and who lead with innovation, courage and commitment.\n\nThe awards underscore the critical role that directors play in terms of best governance practices that build and sustain stakeholder value.\n\nHonorees are top board governance leaders whose leadership skills have helped guide their company’s success and who raise the bar for governance best practices in the boardrooms in our community.', '15-Jul-16', 0, 0, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(610, 'Cincinnati Busness Courier', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'Help the Business Courier identify and recognize the Cincinnati-area employers that have the most engaged workforces. A special publication will be created by the Courier profiling the finalists and winners.\nThe format is an online, anonymous survey of employees consisting of about 50 questions. The survey is conducted through an independent market research company Quantum Workplace.\nThe contest is open to any company located in the 17-county Greater Cincinnati region with more than 10 employees.', '19-Aug-16', 0, 0, 'Cincinnati', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Rob Daumeyer', 'rdaumeyer@bizjournals.com', '', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/nomination', '', ''),
(611, 'Columbus Business First', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'Columbus Business First invites you to nominate individuals for this prestigious award! Forty Under 40 honorees will be highlighted in a special supplement published in the May 27, 2016 issue of Business First.\n\nThe longest-running awards program at Business First, Forty Under 40 is in its 24th year and recognizes young “movers and shakers” in the community. The 40 honorees, who are under the age of 40, are judged on their outstanding career achievements and community service.', '26-Feb-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and the 40 ', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Individual', 'Age', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', ''),
(612, 'Columbus Business First', 'Corporate Caring Awards', 2016, 'The Corporate Caring Awards Program honors for-profit companies for their financial contributions, volunteer service and other unique contributions to Columbus'' charities and nonprofit organizations.There are five award categories in which judges choose one small, one medium, and one large company. The categories represent the type of nonprofits in which a company focuses their giving, based on the information provided. ', '8-Apr-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and the 40 ', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', ''),
(613, 'Columbus Business First', 'C-Suite Awards', 2016, 'The C-Suite Awards honor C-level executives of for profit companies, nonprofits and government agencies for their unique contributions to their organizations and to the Central Ohio community.', '16-May-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', 'JUDGING:   Judging is based on a 30-point scale, with a maximum of 10 points allocated for each of the main nomination sections. Six judges with diverse professions will individually read and score each nomination.  Judges’ scores are combined and the 40 ', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', ''),
(614, 'Columbus Business First', 'Fast 50 Awards', 2016, '2016 will mark the 21st anniversary of the Fast 50 Awards in Columbus. We invite you to submit an application to Columbus Business First''s Fast 50 Program.\nELIGIBILITY\nAll nominees must:\nBe independent, for-profit and privately held\nHave an average of at least $1 million in revenue per year for the past three years\nBe headquartered the Central Ohio region  (Delaware, Fairfield, Franklin, Hocking, Licking, Madison, Morrow, Perry, Pickaway or Union counties)\nHave a three-year operating sales history', '1-Jul-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', 'Financial information used to compile the rankings is kept confidential by our accounting partner and is not made available to Business First or other sponsors of the Fast 50 program. Sales-growth percentage is calculated by subtracting revenue two years ', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/', '', ''),
(615, 'Columbus Business First', 'Best Places to Work Awards', 2016, 'Think you''re employed at one of the best places to work in Central Ohio? You’re in the right place!  Filling out this form will begin the registration process for 2016 Best Places to Work research project.  Please read the following details carefully and complete the nomination form. We will use this contact information in mid-July 2016 to verify your continued interest in participating in the program.\n \nThe Best Places to Work program highlights companies in Central Ohio whose operations are changing the business landscape.  Business First will profile those who are doing their best to foster a great workplace. Last year, 235 companies entered and the top 51 were honored at a high energy luncheon. Don''t miss out -- nominate your company today!', '22-Jul-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2013', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/62831', '', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/'),
(616, 'Columbus Business First', 'BizTech Awards', 2016, 'Help Columbus Business First recognize the people, organizations and companies making an impact on technology and innovation in our community. The BizTech Awards celebrate those contributing to a culture of technology leadership and innovation in the Columbus region. Nominate individuals and organizations that contribute to the Columbus region’s growing reputation as a leader in technology innovation.', '16-Sep-16', 0, 0, '', 'OH', 'USA', 'US Midwest', '', '', 'Annual', 'Melissa Price', 'mprice@bizjournals.com', '614-220-5436', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', '', '2013', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/62831', '', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/columbus/nomination/'),
(617, 'Daily Business Review', 'On the Rise', 2015, 'The DBR On The Rise program recognizes the region’s 40 most promising lawyers under the age of 40 as of Jan. To qualify, the lawyers must work in South Florida. Nominations should be sent to dbrrecognition@alm.com. We''re looking for lawyers who have wielded influence in their practice areas in South Florida\nand beyond. They should be innovators, developing unique practice niches, amassing robust\nbooks of business, demonstrating strong leadership qualities, showing expertise in litigation or\ntransactional work, and committing themselves to pro bono, charitable and professional\nvolunteer work.\nFor this contest, we are asking you to provide:\n1. An essay of no more than 500 words describing why the nominee should be selected. Among\nthe questions that you should attempt to answer:\n• What accomplishments in the last year qualify the nominee for our list? What makes the\nnominee stand out from his or her peers?\n• How has the nominee demonstrated leadership — in their practice, in the workplace and\nin the profession?\n• Has the nominee contributed to the community through pro bono work, charitable work\nor public service? Please describe.\n2. A biography of the nominee, including the following information:\n• Employer\n• Title\n• City and state\n• Birthdates\n• Educations\n• Legal work experience including notable cases, transactions and clients, dates and\nemployer names\n• Other relevant information such as awards, affiliations and significant publications\n3. A high-resolution photo of the nominee.\n4. Contact information for two references who can be contacted for an on-the-record\nconversation about the nominee’s legal work and accomplishments.', '1-Jun-15', 0, 1, '', 'FL', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Catherine Wilson', 'cwilson@alm.com', '305-347-6611', 'Individual', 'Age', '2014', 'http://pdfserver.amlaw.com/dbr/2015-On-the-Rise-Nomination-Form.pdf', 'http://www.dailybusinessreview.com/', ''),
(618, 'Daily Journal', 'Top Plaintiff Lawyers', 2015, 'In this inaugural list of top plaintiff lawyers, the Daily Journal seeks to honor lawyers bringing single cases and multi-party actions in antitrust, labor & employment, environment, personal injury, privacy and data security, product defect and securities and financial fraud. In deciding whether/whom to submit, remember we are looking for impact. How did this attorney’s work impact an industry? The law? The government? Society? All of these questions should be explored and answered in this survey. Matters concerning major issues of the day (making state/national headlines, or cases the industry is following) are given special consideration.\nWe understand many matters are sensitive; however, you must provide the names of matters and clients for all work to be considered for this nomination. We will only contact clients for interviews if the nominee is selected to the list.\nNo extensions to the deadline will be granted. Photos are appreciated but not required. They should be named with the nominee''s last name and bar number and emailed to nominations@dailyjournal.com with the nominee''s full name and bar number in the email subject line.\nNominees must be California Bar members in good standing and based in California although their work can be anywhere in the world.', '12-Jun-15', 0, 1, '', 'CA', 'USA', 'US West', 'Antitrust; Employment Law; Environmental; Litigation; Privacy & Cybersecurity; Corporate Crime & Investigations', 'Personal Injury: Plaintiff; Data Security; Fraud', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Individual', '', '', 'https://www.dailyjournal.com/public/PubMain.cfm?seloption=nomsub&pubdate=showRtBar&shNewsType=nomsub&NewsId=-1&sdivId=&screenHt=770', 'https://www.dailyjournal.com/public/PubMain.cfm', ''),
(619, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Who''s Who in DFW Health Care', 2015, 'We''re looking for the most influential business people in North Texas health care. Eligibility Requirements\n\nEveryone knows it takes great doctors and outstanding nurses to deliver top-flight medical care. Less celebrated is the extensive business-to-business network that makes our health care system tick.\n\nConsider nominating North Texas leaders who specialize in the business aspects of health care. Nominees may be entrepreneurs or executives in any field, including accounting, consulting, device manufacturing, diagnostic services, education, finance, information technology, insurance, law, pharmacy, professional and trade organizations, public policy, real estate and staffing.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: The judges will base their decisions solely on the information provided on the nomination forms. Provide detailed information so the judges can give the nominee full consideration. You may wish to print out the nomination form first and review the questions before submitting your responses online.\n\nPrevious winners of this award are eligible to win again, however their nomination must demonstrate why they are still relevent as well as any new achievements and accomplishments since their previous win.', '12-Jun-15', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', 'Healthcare', 'Health care', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(620, 'Dallas Business Journal', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'The Dallas Business Journal is searching for executives and entrepreneurs in the North Texas business community under the age of 40 for our annual 40 Under 40 Awards. To qualify, nominees must be 39 years old or younger as of May 20, 2016. Tell us about your nominee''s proven track record in both business and community involvement. We are looking for executives who stand out — innovators, deal makers and heavy hitters who excel in their companies and industries and still make time for their communities.', '15-Mar-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Age', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination/', '', ''),
(621, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Middle Market 50', 2016, 'This second annual research project of the Dallas Business Journal ranks the fastest-growing companies in Dallas-Fort Worth with annual revenue of $25 million to $750 million, based on revenue growth over a three-year period.\n\nTo participate, companies must provide revenue figures for 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2015 for use in calculating the percentage of revenue growth during that period. This information will be published in the final Middle Market 50 list.\nBoth private and public companies are eligible to participate. Companies must be headquartered in North Texas. Regional offices or subsidiaries will not be considered for this particular list. ', '22-Apr-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Company; Organization; Law Firm', 'Community or Civic', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination/', '', ''),
(622, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Best Places to Work', 2016, 'Nominate your company for the Dallas Business Journal''s 14th annual Best Places to Work Awards!\nEligibility Requirements\nTo get started, complete this form and follow the steps below. You''ll find answers to frequently asked questions below, as well. \nIn order to be considered, your company must have a minimum of 10 employees in the seven-county North Texas region: Dallas, Collin, Denton, Tarrant, Rockwall, Ellis and Kaufman counties. Company headquarters may be elsewhere. Eligibility is determined solely by the number of North Texas employees.', '20-May-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '(402) 408-4162', 'Company; Law Firm; Organization', 'Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(623, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Women in Business Awards', 2016, 'The Dallas Business Journal''s ninth annual Women in Business Awards will honor the North Texas'' most influential business women. We''re looking for women from every industry and profession — women who have made a difference in their workplace, blaze trails for other women and are leaving a mark on their communities. ', '10-Jun-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Women; Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(624, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Women in Technology Awards', 2016, 'The Dallas Business Journal’s 2016 North Texas Women in Technology Awards honor tech-focused women who drive innovation, lead technology companies and shape the local community.', '29-Jul-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Women; Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(625, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'CFO of the Year Awards', 2016, 'Nominees should be either a chief financial officer or hold an equivalent position at a company or organization based in North Texas.. The CFO of the Year Awards are given to the chief financial officers and their teams who deliver the most outstanding performances for their companies. A panel of independent judges, drawn from the region''s top financial leaders, will determine the winners based on criteria that will include:\nDemonstrated financial growth during the year\nSuccess in overcoming significant business challenges or barriers\nExamples of team leadership and superior management\nOther factors may include a chief financial officer''s contributions to the community (such as social, nonprofit or charitable giving)\nDemonstrated commitment to the company''s financial best practices and accounting standards, or success as a strategic visionary for the enterprise', '19-Aug-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', 'Banking & Finance', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(626, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Who''s Who in Energy', 2016, 'The Dallas Business Journal is seeking nominations for the multistate ''Who''s Who in Energy'' publication.\n\nBusiness journals in multiple cities — Dallas, Denver, Houston, Pittsburgh, St. Louis and San Antonio — will partner on this undertaking. The result? A listing of some 700 business leaders across sectors and states who are making energy deals happen and/or working on behalf of energy companies. The list will be published in the Nov. 27 issue of the DBJ.\n \nHonorees can work in a number of positions throughout the energy industry, including finance, law, engineering and energy companies themselves.', '2-Sep-16', 1, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', 'Energy & Natural Resources', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', ''),
(627, 'Dallas Business Journal', 'Outstanding Directors Awards', 2016, 'The 2016 Outstanding Directors Awards honor individual directors and full boards of directors that demonstrate the vital leadership and business savvy necessary to help guide their businesses’ success.   C-level executives or significant business partners (such as accounting firms, bankers, law firms, compensation advisers and other consultants) are the ideal nominators for this prestigious award recognizing high-performing directors or boards. We welcome nominations from anyone with first-hand knowledge of a board’s or board member’s achievements.\n   ', '9-Sep-16', 0, 0, 'Dallas', 'TX', 'USA', 'US South', '', '', 'Annual', 'Anna Butler', 'abutler@bizjournals.com', '', 'Individual', 'Community or Civic', '2014', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/nomination', ''),
(628, 'International Financial Law Review', 'Financial and Corporate Research', 2016, 'The IFLR1000 Financial and corporate research is now entering its 27th annual edition and we invite all relevant law firms to participate in the process.\nThe research process culminates in the publication of law firm rankings, individual lawyer recommendations and law firm reviews (IFLR1000 Reviews).\nThe Financial and corporate research incorporates the following practice areas:\nBanking and finance (banking, financial restructuring, project finance)\nCapital markets (debt, derivatives, equity, structured finance and securitisation)\nCompetition *\nCorporate and M&A (M&A and private equity)\nFinancial services regulatory *\nInvestment funds *\nRestructuring and insolvency', '15-Apr-16', 1, 1, '', '', 'Ireland', 'Europe', 'Banking and Finance; Capital markets: Debt; Capital markets: Equity; Financial services regulatory; Investment funds; M&A; Project finance; Restructuring and insolvency)', '', 'Annual', 'Sam Duke', 'sduke@iflr1000.com', '', 'Law Firm', '', '', '', '', ''),
