(858, 'The Lawyer', 'Infrastructure Projects Team of the Year', 2016, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout transaction from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThis category is open to firms involved in international projects as well as UK PPP and PFI work.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nSensitivity to political/local considerations\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm; Legal Department', '', '', '', '', ''),
(859, 'The Lawyer', 'International Firm of the Year', 2016, 'This category is open to international firms operating globally across any number of jurisdictions; this year we also encourage entries from teams based in the Asia offices of UK or international firms. Entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nDetails of up to five cases / deals which demonstrate:\nClear market-leading strategic vision for the region \nDepth and breadth of expertise\nConsistent delivery of client service\nCommercial strength\nMarket share and evidence of both growth and retention within their client list\nLegal and/or entrepreneurial innovation\nA list of key clients and local client wins\nAny other information which demonstrates progress made throughout the year, for example:\nYear on year growth in business activity\nFinancial performance\nClearly identifiable strategy\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nKey hires and investment', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm', '', '', '', '', ''),
(860, 'The Lawyer', 'IP Team of the Year', 2016, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter from 1st April 2015 until the present time.\nThis category includes IP and data protection rights as well as IT and Telecoms. The entries may be contentious as well as non-contentious. \nThe entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen deal including:\nMarket context\nHistory of client relationship\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm; Legal Department', '', '', '', '', ''),
(861, 'The Lawyer', 'Law Firm of the Year', 2016, 'This category is open to any firm headquartered in the UK; entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nEntries will not be judged on organisational size and turnover alone, but on the clarity of the strategic vision demonstrated.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nEvidence of:\nStrategic vision and strong leadership\nStrong financial management and growth\nInnovation in client service delivery \nInnovation in pricing\nExcellence in their chosen sector(s)\nExcellent talent management and workplace development\nSignificant client wins and feedback\nRecent hires and investment\nLeadership team brief (including biographies)', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm', '', '', '', '', ''),
(862, 'The Lawyer', 'Litigation Team of the Year', 2016, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter heard in England and Wales in which judgment was delivered after 1 April 2015.\nAlthough we recognise that it is always preferable to engage in mediation or dispute resolution, this category can only recognise cases that are on public record. The category is open to lawyers specialising in insurance, reinsurance, construction, tax & trusts, defamation, as well as general commercial litigation.\nOngoing cases will not be considered.\nAlthough we welcome entries which are being heard across multiple jurisdictions, a material element of the case must have been heard in the High Court or Appellate Courts of England and Wales. \n The entry form will ask you for:\nFull details of the chosen case including:\nMarket context\nFull list of representation\nHistory of representation – did the representation change?\nTechnical innovation\nInnovation in client service\nInnovation in pricing\nMeasurable outcomes\nA list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel.\nSupporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of:\nInnovation in pricing and service delivery\nClient wins\nFinancial performance\nOutcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve\nPrecedents set\nMultiple entries from one firm are acceptable.  ', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', 'Litigation', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm; Legal Department', '', '', '', '', ''),
(863, 'The Lawyer', 'Offshore Firm of the Year', 2016, 'The entry form will ask you for:\nInformation that demonstrates:\nExcellence in your key jurisdiction\nDepth and breadth of expertise\nCommercial strength, including financial results\nMarket share and evidence of both growth and retention within your client list\nLegal and/or entrepreneurial innovation\nEvidence of market-leading strategy', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm', '', '', '', '', ''),
(864, 'The Lawyer', 'Pro Bono Initiative of the Year', 2016, 'Entries should include details of a lead piece of pro bono work.\nPlease provide evidence of:\na. Innovative thinking\nb. Senior buy-in from across the organisation\nc. Measurable outcomes and how the project generated significant change\nWhere possible please provide testimonials from relevant parties\nPlease provide details of any supporting pro bono work.', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm; Legal Department; Practice Group', 'Pro bono', '', '', '', ''),
(865, 'The Lawyer', 'Real Estate Team of the Year', 2016, 'Entries into this category should focus on one standout matter from 1st April 2015 until the present time. Real estate team of the year is open to commercial property lawyers working in the planning, development, finance or institutional investment arenas. The entry form will ask you for: Full details of the chosen deal including: Market context History of client relationship History of representation – did the representation change? Technical innovation Innovation in client service Innovation in pricing Measurable outcomes A list of all major parties (individuals and firms) involved in the deal, including (where appropriate) key advisers, associates, partners, barristers and in-house counsel. Supporting evidence of the team’s performance over the year, including details of: Innovation in pricing and service delivery Client wins Political sensitivity Financial performance Consistently excellent project management skills Outcomes – what does your work mean to the clients you serve Precedents set Multiple entries from one firm are acceptable.', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm; Legal Department; Practice Group', '', '2015', 'http://www.thelawyerawards.com/categories', '', ''),
(866, 'The Lawyer', 'Regional Firm of the Year', 2016, 'This category is open to any firm headquartered in the UK outside of London; entries should cover work undertaken and progress made over the course of the year from April 2015 to the present day. \nEntries will not be judged on organisational size and turnover alone, but on the clarity of the strategic vision demonstrated.\nThe entry form will ask you for:\nEvidence of:\nStrategic vision and strong leadership\nStrong financial management and growth\nInnovation in client service delivery \nInnovation in pricing\nExcellence in their chosen sector(s)\nExcellent talent management and workplace development\nSignificant client wins and feedback\nRecent hires and investment\nLeadership team brief (including biographies)\nAn outline of the particular challenges faced by the firm and its peers in current market conditions, and explain how these challenges have been overcome.', '4-Mar-16', 0, 1, '', '', '', 'Europe', '', '', 'Annual', 'Sarah Hetherington', 'sarah.hetherington@centaurmedia.com', '4020 7970 4532', 'Law Firm', '', '', '', '', ''),
(867, 'The Network Journal', '25 Influential Black Women in Business', 2016, 'Launched in March 1999, The Network Journal''s 25 Influential Black Women in Business Awards honors women whose professional achievements have significantly impacted an industry or profession, and who also have made an important contribution to their community. A ''TNJ25'' honoree typically is a business owner, or a partner, president, CEO, board chair, or other senior-management executive with significant decision-making authority in the corporate, nonprofit (including academia and medicine), or government sector.', '5-Feb-16', 0, 0, '', 'NY', 'USA', 'US Northeast', '', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Individual', 'Minority; Women', '', 'http://www.tnj.com/25-Influential-black-women/2015', '', ''),
(868, 'The Network Journal', '40 Under 40', 2016, 'THE SEARCH IS ON. We are searching for the most dynamic business and professional leaders under the age of 40. We''re looking for candidates who share a commitment to business growth and professional excellence and to the community.\n \nThe 19th Annual 40 Under Forty Achievement Awards will honor this new generation of men and women who are making headlines in their fields. Winners will be featured in the special issue of The Network Journal, June 2016. Anyone who is 39 years or younger on or before June 15, 2016 is eligible.', '5-Feb-16', 0, 0, '', 'NY', 'USA', 'US Northeast', '', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Individual', 'Age', '2015', 'http://www.tnj.com/40-under-forty/call-for-nominations', '', ''),
(869, 'Washington Business Journal', 'CFO of the Year', 2016, 'This award honors the region''s top financial professionals in Greater Washington for outstanding performance in their roles as corporate financial stewards.  Nominees should be either a chief financial officer or hold an equivalent position at a company or organization based in D.C. or one of the following jurisdictions: Alexandria, Arlington, Fairfax, Prince William and Loudoun counties in Virginia and Prince George''s and Montgomery counties in Maryland. ', '29-Apr-16', 0, 0, '', 'DC', 'USA', 'US Mid-Atlantic', '', '', 'Annual', '', '', '', 'Individual', '', '2015', 'http://www.bizjournals.com/washington/nomination/79622#eligibility', '', ''),
